 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">Methods</div>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The Stata 14.0 statistical program is employed for data management, analysis and graphing [
  <a rid="pone.0138208.ref021" ref-type="bibr" href="#pone.0138208.ref021">21</a>]. 
  <span class="bold">Figs 
   <a rid="pone.0138208.g001" ref-type="fig" href="#pone.0138208.g001">1</a>
  </span>and 
  <span class="bold">
   <a rid="pone.0138208.g002" ref-type="fig" href="#pone.0138208.g002">2</a>
  </span>chart response percentages calculated using probability weights as described above. Ninety-five percent confidence intervals appear with each data point in the time plots of 
  <a rid="pone.0138208.g002" ref-type="fig" href="#pone.0138208.g002">Fig 2</a>.
 </p>
